# Vercel AI SDK Rules

## Setup
- ALWAYS use `ai` package (Vercel AI SDK v4+)
- Import providers from `@ai-sdk/openai`, `@ai-sdk/anthropic` etc.
- NEVER call OpenAI/Anthropic APIs directly — use AI SDK abstractions
- Store API keys in `.env.local`, NEVER commit them

## Streaming — Always Stream
- ALWAYS use `streamText()` for chat responses — never `generateText()` for UX
- Return `result.toDataStreamResponse()` from API routes
- Client: use `useChat()` hook from `ai/react`
- NEVER block UI waiting for full response

## API Route Pattern
- AI routes: `app/api/chat/route.ts`, `app/api/ai/[action]/route.ts`
- ALWAYS set `maxDuration = 30` for streaming routes (Vercel timeout)
- ALWAYS validate user auth before any AI call
- ALWAYS track usage to prevent abuse

## Model Selection
- Default: `openai('gpt-4o-mini')` for cost efficiency
- Complex tasks: `openai('gpt-4o')` or `anthropic('claude-sonnet-4-6')`
- ALWAYS make model configurable via env var

## System Prompts
- ALWAYS define system prompts in `lib/ai/prompts.ts`
- NEVER hardcode system prompts in route handlers
- USE template literals for dynamic context injection

## Example — Streaming Chat Route
```typescript
// app/api/chat/route.ts
import { openai } from '@ai-sdk/openai'
import { streamText } from 'ai'
import { auth } from '@clerk/nextjs/server'

export const maxDuration = 30

export async function POST(req: Request) {
  const { userId } = await auth()
  if (!userId) {
    return new Response('Unauthorized', { status: 401 })
  }

  const { messages } = await req.json()

  const result = streamText({
    model: openai('gpt-4o-mini'),
    system: 'You are a helpful assistant for a Next.js SaaS application.',
    messages,
    maxTokens: 1000,
  })

  return result.toDataStreamResponse()
}
```

